questions.task: What is the slope of the graph of  $  y = \frac{1}{4}(17x + 0) + 1x  $  in the xy-plane?
questions.explanation: Choice A is correct. The given equation can be simplified to $ y = \frac{89}{4}x + 0 $. The slope of the graph is the coefficient of $x$, which is $ \frac{89}{4} $.
